description:
&lt;p&gt;As part of our current local transformation work Nottinghamshire Healthcare Trust have received investment to support expansion of the Ashfield Local Mental Health Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you welcome a new challenge? If you are a confident experienced clinician and would like an opportunity to use your skills working in a busy, challenging, rewarding and supportive environment we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a range of mental health practitioners from a nursing, social care or OT background who want to gain experience from working with a variety of mental health conditions within the community to join our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The core aspects of the role will involve conducting assessments of individuals when they are referred to the Local Mental Health Team, Care Coordinate with a view to managing risk and developing a person centred care plan that will enable the individual to manage their mental health condition. The role will also involve being part of a duty worker system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would welcome applications from candidates interested in either full or part time contracts. This is an excellent opportunity for both experienced and newly qualified people to explore the options for on - going careers in community mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full UK driving licence and vehicle for business use is required for this post; however reasonable adjustments will be made for disabled individuals in line with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Becky Jones, Clinical Team Leader, 0115 9560858&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ian Lerway, Clinical Team Leader, 0115 9560858&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*The closing date given is a guide. We reserve the right to close the post early once we have received a sufficient number of applicants, so we advise you to submit your application early to prevent disappointment. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*We will be requesting references by email.  Please ensure you include email addresses and contact numbers for your referees to avoid delay in the recruitment process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
